obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (38169)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38169&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Railway Claims`
  line `Tribunal Act, 1987.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 8th November, 1989, vide notification No. S.O. 783(E), dated 5th October, 1989, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (38170)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38170&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "application" means an application made under section 16;`
  line
  line `(b) "appointed day" means the date^1 with effect from which the Claims Tribunal is established`
  line `under section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) "Bench" means a Bench of the Claims Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(d) "Chairman" means the Chairman of the Claims Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(e) "Claims Tribunal" means the Railway Claims Tribunal established under section 3;`
  line
  line `(f) "Judicial Member" means a Member of the Claims Tribunal appointed as such under this Act,`
  line `and includes the Chairman or Vice-Chairman who possesses any of the qualifications specified in`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(g) "Member" means a Member (whether Judicial or Technical) of the Claims Tribunal, and`
  line `includes the Chairman and Vice-Chairman;`
  line
  line `(h) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(i) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules;`
  line
  line `(j) "Railways Act" means the Indian Railways Act, 1890 (9 of 1890);`
  line
  line `(k) "rules" means rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(l) "Technical Member" means a Member of the Claims Tribunal who is not a Judicial Member,`
  line `and includes the Chairman or a Vice-Chairman who possesses any of the qualifications specified in`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(m) "Vice-Chairman" means a Vice-Chairman of the Claims Tribunal.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--References to the Vice-Chairman in this Act shall be construed as references to`
  line `each of the Vice-Chairman;`
  line
  line `^2[(n) "untoward incident" shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (c) of section 123 of the`
  line `Railways Act, 1989;]`
  line
  line `^3[(o)] words and expressions used and not defined in this Act but defined in the Railways Act or`
  line `the rules made thereunder shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act or the`
  line `said rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 8th November, 1989, vide notification No. S.O. 784(E), dated 5th October, 1989, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3 (ii)`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 28 of 1994, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-8-1994).`
  line
  line `3. Clause (n) re-lettered as clause (o) thereof by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (38171)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of Railway Claims Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 162 (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38171&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall, by notification,`
  line `establish a Claims Tribunal, to be known as the Railway Claims Tribunal, to exercise the jurisdiction,`
  line `powers and authority conferred on it by or under this Act ^1`
  line `[and under Chapter VII of the Railways`
  line `Act,1989 (24 of 1989).]`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (38172)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Composition of Claims Tribunal and Benches thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38172&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Claims Tribunal shall consist`
  line `of a Chairman, four Vice-Chairmen and such number of Judicial Members and Technical Members as the`
  line `Central Government may deem fit and, subject to the other provisions of this Act, the jurisdiction, powers`
  line `and authority of the Claims Tribunal may be exercised by Benches thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, a Bench shall consist of one Judicial Member and one`
  line `Technical Member.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Chairman--`
  line
  line `(a) may, in addition to discharging the functions of the Judicial Member or the Technical Member`
  line `of the Bench to which he is appointed, discharge the functions of the Judicial Member or, as the case`
  line `may be, the Technical Member, of any other Bench;`
  line
  line `(b) may transfer a Vice-Chairman or other Member from one Bench to another Bench;`
  line
  line `(c) may authorise the Vice-Chairman or the Judicial Member or the Technical Member appointed`
  line `to one Bench to discharge also the functions of the Vice-Chairman or, as the case may be, the Judicial`
  line `Member or the Technical Member of another Bench.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this section, it shall be`
  line `competent for the Chairman or any other Member authorised by the Chairman in this behalf to function as`
  line `a Bench consisting of a single Member and exercise the jurisdiction, powers and authority of the Claims`
  line `Tribunal in respect of such classes of cases or such matters pertaining to such classes of cases as the`
  line `Chairman may, by general or special order, specify:`
  line
  line `Provided that if at any stage of the hearing of any such case or matter, it appears to the Chairman or`
  line `such Member that the case or matter is of such a nature that it ought to be heard by a Bench consisting of`
  line `two Members, the case or matter may be transferred by the Chairman or, as the case may be, referred to`
  line `him for transfer, to such Bench as the Chairman may deem fit.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, the Benches shall sit at such places as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, specify.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (38173)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Qualifications for appointment as Chairman, Vice-Chairman or other Member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38173&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) A`
  line `person shall not be qualified for appointment as the Chairman unless he--`
  line
  line `(a) is, or has been, a Judge of a High Court; or`
  line
  line `(b) has, for at least two years, held the office of a Vice-Chairman.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as the Vice-Chairman unless he--`
  line
  line `(a) is, or has been, or is qualified to be, a Judge of a High Court; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been a member of the Indian Legal Service and has held a post in Grade I of that Service`
  line `or any higher post for at least five years; or`
  line
  line `(c) has, for at least five years, held a civil judicial post carrying a scale of pay which is not less`
  line `than that of a Joint Secretary to the Government of India; or`
  line
  line `(d) has, for at least five years, held a post under a railway administration carrying a scale of pay`
  line `which is not less than that of a Joint Secretary to the Government of India and has adequate`
  line `knowledge of rules and procedure of, and experience in, claims and commercial matters relating to`
  line `railways; or`
  line
  line `(e) has, for a period of not less than three years, held office as a Judicial Member or a Technical`
  line Member.
  line
  line `(3) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as a Judicial Member unless he--`
  line
  line `(a) is, or has been, or is qualified to be, a Judge of a High Court; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been a Member of the Indian Legal Service and has held a post in Grade I of that Service`
  line `for at least three years; or`
  line
  line `(c) has, for at least three years, held a civil judicial post carrying a scale of pay which is not less`
  line `than that of a Joint Secretary to the Government of India.`
  line
  line `(4) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as a Technical Member unless he has, for at least`
  line `three years, held a post under a railway administration carrying a scale of pay which is not less than that`
  line `of a Joint Secretary to the Government of India and has adequate knowledge of rules and procedure of,`
  line `and experience in, claims and commercial matters relating to railways.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (6), the Chairman, Vice-Chairman and every other`
  line `Member shall be appointed by the President.`
  line
  line `(6) No appointment of a person as the Chairman shall be made except after consultation with the`
  line `Chief Justice of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (38174)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Vice-Chairman to act as Chairman or to discharge his functions in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38174&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) In`
  line `the event of the occurrence of any vacancy in the office of the Chairman by reason of his death,`
  line `resignation or otherwise, such one of the Vice-Chairman as the Central Government may, by notification,`
  line `authorise in this behalf, shall act as the Chairman until the date on which a new Chairman, appointed in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act to fill such vacancy, enters upon his office.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Chairman is unable to discharge his functions owing to absence, illness or any other`
  line `cause, such one of the Vice-Chairmen as the Central Government may, by notification, authorise in this`
  line `behalf,shall discharge the functions of the Chairman until the date on which the Chairman resumes his`
  line duties.
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (38175)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Term of office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38175&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The Chairman, Vice-Chairman or other Member shall hold office as such for a`
  line `term of five years from the date on which he enters upon his office or until he attains,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of the Chairman, the age of sixty-five years; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of the Vice-Chairman or any other Member, the age of sixty-two years,`
  line
  line `whichever is earlier.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (38176)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Resignation and removal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38176&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairman, Vice-Chairman or other Member may, by notice`
  line `in writing under his hand addressed to the President, resign his office:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairman, Vice-Chairman or other Member shall, unless he is permitted by the`
  line `President to relinquish his office sooner, continue to hold office until the expiry of three months from the`
  line `date of receipt of such notice or until a person duly appointed as his successor enters upon his office or`
  line `until the expiry of his term of office, whichever is the earliest.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman, Vice-Chairman or any other Member shall not be removed from his office except`
  line `by an order made by the President on the ground of proved misbehaviour or incapacity after an inquiry`
  line `made by a Judge of the Supreme Court in which such Chairman, Vice-Chairman or other Member had`
  line `been informed of the charges against him and given a reasonable opportunity of being heard in respect of`
  line `those charges.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by rules, regulate the procedure for the investigation of`
  line `misbehaviour or incapacity of the Chairman, Vice-Chairman or other Member referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (38199)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Salaries and allowances and other terms and conditions of service of Chairman, Vice-Chairman and other Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38199&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and`
  line `conditions of service (including pension, gratuity and other retirement benefits) of, the Chairman,`
  line `Vice-Chairman and other Members shall be such as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that neither the salary and allowances nor the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Chairman, Vice-Chairman or other Members shall be varied to his disadvantage after his appointment.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9_a:
  sectionId (49418)
  sectionNo 9A
  orderNo 10
  title `Qualifications, terms and conditions of service of Chairman, Vice-Chairman and Member`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=49418&sectionno=9A&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[9A. Qualifications, terms and conditions of service of Chairman, Vice-Chairman and`
  line `Member.--Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the qualifications, appointment, term of`
  line `office, salaries and allowances, resignation, removal and other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Chairman, Vice-Chairman and other Members of the Tribunal appointed after the commencement of ^2[the`
  line `Tribunals Reforms Act, 2021, shall be governed by the provisions of Chapter II of the said Act]:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairman, Vice-Chairman and Members appointed before the commencement of`
  line `Part XIV of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017, shall continue to be governed by the provisions of this`
  line `Act, and the rules made thereunder as if the provisions of section 184 of the Finance Act, 2017, had not`
  line `come into force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 162 (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 16, for Part XIV of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017, shall be governed by the provisions of section 184 of that Act (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (38200)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Provision as to the holding of offices by Chairman, Vice-Chairman, etc., on ceasing to be such Chairman or Vice-Chairman, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38200&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `On ceasing to hold office--`
  line
  line `(a) the Chairman of the Claims Tribunal shall be ineligible for further employment either under`
  line `the Government of India or under the Government of a State;`
  line
  line `(b) a Vice-Chairman shall, subject to the other provisions of this Act, be eligible for appointment`
  line `as the Chairman of the Claims Tribunal, or as the chairman, vice-chairman or member of any other`
  line `Tribunal established under any law for the time being in force, but not for any other employment`
  line `either under the Government of India or under the Government of a State;`
  line
  line `(c) a Member (other than the Chairman or Vice-Chairman) shall, subject to the other provisions`
  line `of this Act, be eligible for appointment as the Chairman or Vice-Chairman or as the chairman,`
  line `vice-chairman or member of any other Tribunal established under any law for the time being in force,`
  line `but not for any other employment either under the Government of India or under the Government of a`
  line State;
  line
  line `(d) the Chairman, Vice-Chairman or other Member shall not appear, act or plead before the`
  line `Claims Tribunal.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, employment under the Government of India or under`
  line `the Government of a State includes employment under any local or other authority within the territory of`
  line `India or under the control of the Government of India or under any corporation or society owned or`
  line `controlled by the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (38179)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Financial and administrative powers of Chairman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38179&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The Chairman shall exercise such`
  line `financial and administrative powers over the Benches as may be vested in him under the rules:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairman shall have authority to delegate such of his financial and administrative`
  line `powers as he may think fit to the Vice-Chairman or any other officer of the Claims Tribunal, subject to`
  line `the condition that the Vice-Chairman or such officer shall, while exercising such delegated powers,`
  line `continue to act under the direction, control and supervision of the Chairman.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (38180)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Staff of Claims Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38180&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall determine the nature and`
  line `categories of the officers and other employees required to assist the Claims Tribunal in the discharge of`
  line `its functions and provide the Claims Tribunal with such officers and other employees as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The officers and other employees of the Claims Tribunal shall discharge their functions under the`
  line `general superintendence of the Chairman.`
  line
  line `(3) The salaries and allowances and conditions of service of the officers and other employees of the`
  line `Claims Tribunal shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (38181)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Jurisdiction, powers and authority of Claims Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38181&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Claims Tribunal shall`
  line `exercise, on and from the appointed day, all such jurisdiction, powers and authority as were exercisable`
  line `immediately before that day by any civil court or a Claims Commissioner appointed under the provisions`
  line `of the Railways Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) relating to the responsibility of the railway administrations as carriers under Chapter VII of`
  line `the Railways Act in respect of claims for--`
  line
  line `(i) compensation for loss, destruction, damage, deterioration or non-delivery of animals or`
  line `goods entrusted to a railway administration for carriage by railway;`
  line
  line `(ii) compensation payable under section 82A of the Railways Act or the rules made`
  line `thereunder; and`
  line
  line `(b) in respect of the claims for refund of fares or part thereof or for refund of any freight paid in`
  line `respect of animals or goods entrusted to a railway administration to be carried by railway.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(1A) The Claims Tribunal shall also exercise, on and from the date of commencement of the`
  line `provisions of section 124A of the Railways Act, 1989 (24 of 1989), all such jurisdiction, powers and`
  line `authority as were exercisable immediately before that date by any civil court in respect of claims for`
  line `compensation now payable by the railway administration under section 124A of the said Act or the rules`
  line `made thereunder.]`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(1B) The Claims Tribunal shall also exercise, on and from the commencement of Part XIV of`
  line `Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017 (7 of 2017), the jurisdiction, powers and authority conferred on the`
  line `Tribunal under Chapter VII of the Railways Act,1989 (24 of 1989).]`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of the ^3`
  line `[Railways Act, 1989 (24 of 1989)] and the rules made thereunder shall, so`
  line `far as may be, be applicable to the inquiring into or determining, any claims by the Claims Tribunal under`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 1994, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-8-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 162 (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 28 of 1994, s. 9, for "Railways Act" (w.e.f 1-8-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (38182)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Distribution of business amongst Benches.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38182&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any Benches are constituted, the`
  line `Central Government may, from time to time, by notification, make provisions as to the distribution of the`
  line `business of the Claims Tribunal amongst the Benches and specify the matters which may be dealt with by`
  line `each Bench.`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises as to whether any matter falls within the purview of the business allocated to`
  line `a Bench, the decision of the Chairman shall be final.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the expression "matters" includes`
  line `an application under section 20.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (38183)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Bar of jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs by Act 7 of 2017, s. 162, for "sub-sections (1) and (1A)" (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38183&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, no court or other authority shall have, or`
  line `be entitled to, exercise any jurisdiction, powers or authority in relation to the matters referred to in`
  line ^1
  line `[sub-sections (1), (1A) and (1B)] of section 13.`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (38184)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 17
  title `Application to Claims Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38184&sectionno=16&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person seeking any relief in respect of the matters`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1)`
  line `^1[or sub-section (1A)] of section 13 may make an application to the Claims`
  line Tribunal.
  line
  line `(2) Every application under sub-section (1) shall be in such form and be accompanied by such`
  line `documents or other evidence and by such fee in respect of the filing of such application and by such other`
  line `fees for the service or execution of processes as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such fee shall be payable in respect of an application under sub-clause (ii) of`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (1)`
  line `^2[or, as the case may be, sub-section (1A)] of section 13.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 11, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 28 of 1994, s.11 (w.e.f. 1-8-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (38185)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title Limitation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38185&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Claims Tribunal shall not admit an application for any claim`
  line
  line `(a) under sub-clause (i) of clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 13 unless the application is`
  line `made within three years from the date on which the goods in question were entrusted to the railway`
  line `administration for carriage by railway;`
  line
  line `(b) under sub-clause (ii) of clause (a) of sub-section (1)`
  line ^1
  line `[or, as the case may be,`
  line `sub-section (1A)] of section 13 unless the application is made within one year of occurrence of the`
  line accident;
  line
  line `(c) under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 13 unless the application is made within three`
  line `years from the date on which the fare or freight is paid to the railway administration:`
  line
  line `Provided that no application for any claim referred to in sub-clause (i) of clause (a) of sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 13 shall be preferred to the Claims Tribunal until the expiration of three months next after the`
  line `date on which the intimation of the claim has been preferred under section 78B of the Railways Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), an application may be entertained after the`
  line `period specified in sub-section (1) if the applicant satisfies the Claims Tribunal that he had sufficient`
  line `cause for not making the application within such period.`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (38186)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title `Procedure and powers of Claims Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38186&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Claims Tribunal shall not be bound by the`
  line `procedure laid down by the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), but shall be guided by the`
  line `principles of natural justice and, subject to the other provisions of this Act and of any rules, the Claims`
  line `Tribunal shall have powers to regulate its own procedure including the fixing of places and times of its`
  line enquiry.
  line
  line `(2) The Claims Tribunal shall decide every application as expeditiously as possible and ordinarily`
  line `every application shall be decided on a perusal of documents, written representations and affidavits and`
  line `after hearing such oral arguments as may be advanced.`
  line
  line `(3) The Claims Tribunal shall have, for the purposes of discharging its functions under this Act, the`
  line `same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while`
  line `trying a suit, in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) subject to the provisions of sections 123 and 124 of the Indian Evidence`
  line `Act, 1872 (1 of 1872), requisitioning any public record or document or copy of such record or`
  line `document from any office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(f) reviewing its decisions;`
  line
  line `(g) dismissing an application for default or deciding it ex parte;`
  line
  line `(h) setting aside any order of dismissal of any application for default or any order passed by it`
  line `ex parte;`
  line
  line `(i) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (38187)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 20
  title `Right to legal representation and presenting officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38187&sectionno=19&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person making an application to`
  line `the Claims Tribunal may either appear in person or take the assistance of a legal practitioner of his choice`
  line `to present his case before the Claims Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) A railway administration may authorise one or more legal practitioners or any of its officers to act`
  line `as presenting officers and every person so authorised by it may present its case with respect to any`
  line `application before the Claims Tribunal.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (38188)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power of Chairman to transfer cases from one Bench to another.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38188&sectionno=20&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `On the application of any`
  line `of the parties and after notice to the parties, and after hearing such of them as he may desire to be heard,`
  line `or on his own motion without such notice, the Chairman may transfer any case pending before one Bench,`
  line `for disposal, to any other Bench.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (38189)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 22
  title `Decision to be by majority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38189&sectionno=21&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `If the Members of a Bench differ in opinion on any point, they`
  line `shall state the point or points on which they differ, and make a reference to the Chairman who shall either`
  line `hear the point or points himself or refer the case for hearing on such point or points by one or more of the`
  line `other Members and such point or points shall be decided according to the opinion of the majority of the`
  line `Members who have heard the case, including those who first heard it.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (38190)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 23
  title `Execution of orders of Claims Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38190&sectionno=22&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) An order made by the Claims Tribunal under this`
  line `Act shall be executable by the Claims Tribunal as a decree of civil court and, for this purpose, the Claims`
  line `Tribunal shall have all the powers of a civil court.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Claims Tribunal may transmit any`
  line `order made by it to a civil court having local jurisdiction and such civil court shall execute the order as if`
  line `it were a decree made by that court.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (38191)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38191&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as provided in sub-section (2) and notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) or in any other law, an appeal shall lie from every order, not`
  line `being an interlocutory order, of the Claims Tribunal, to the High Court having jurisdiction over the place`
  line `where the Bench is located.`
  line
  line `(2) No appeal shall lie from an order passed by the Claims Tribunal with the consent of the parties.`
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal under this section shall be preferred within a period of ninety days from the date of`
  line `the order appealed against.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (38192)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 25
  title `Transfer of pending cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38192&sectionno=24&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every suit, claim or other legal proceeding`
  line `(other than an appeal) pending before any court, Claims Commissioner or other authority immediately`
  line `before the appointed day, ^1`
  line [
  line ^2
  line `[or the date of commencement of the provisions of sub-section (1A), or, as`
  line `the case may be, the date of commencement of the provisions of sub-section (1B)] of section 13], being a`
  line `suit, claim or proceeding the cause of action whereon it is based is such that it would have been, if it had`
  line `arisen after the appointed day, ^1`
  line `[or the date of commencement of the provisions of sub-section (1A), or, as`
  line `the case may be, the date of commencement of the provisions of sub-section (1B)] of section 13], within`
  line `the jurisdiction of the Claims Tribunal, shall stand transferred on ^3`
  line `[that day or, as the case may be, date,]`
  line `to the Claims Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any suit, claim or other legal proceeding stands transferred from any court, Claims`
  line `Commissioner or other authority to the Claims Tribunal under sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) the court, Claims Commissioner or other authority shall, as soon as may be after such transfer,`
  line `forward the records of such suit, claim or other legal proceeding to the Claims Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(b) the Claims Tribunal may, on receipt of such records, proceed to deal with such suit, claim or`
  line `other legal proceeding, so far as may be, in the same manner as an application, from the stage which`
  line `was reached before such transfer or from any earlier stage or de novo as the Claims Tribunal may`
  line `deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 1994, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-8-1994).`
  line
  line `2. Subs by Act 7 of 2017, s. 162 (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 28 of 1994, s. 13, for "that day" (w.e.f. 1-8-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (38193)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 26
  title `Proceedings before Claims Tribunal to be judicial proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38193&sectionno=25&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `All proceedings before the`
  line `Claims Tribunal shall be deemed to be judicial proceedings within the meaning of sections 193, 219 and`
  line `228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (38194)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 27
  title `Members and staff of Claims Tribunal to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38194&sectionno=26&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `The Chairman, Vice-Chairman`
  line `and other Members and the officers and other employees of the Claims Tribunal shall be deemed to be`
  line `public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (38195)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 28
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38195&sectionno=27&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government or against the Chairman, Vice-Chairman or other Member, or any`
  line `other person authorised by the Chairman, Vice-Chairman or other Member for anything which is in good`
  line `faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or any rule or order made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (38196)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 29
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38196&sectionno=28&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force or in any instrument`
  line `having effect by virtue of any law other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (38197)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 30
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38197&sectionno=29&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions,`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of three years from the`
  line `appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (38198)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=38198&sectionno=30&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules to carry`
  line `out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may provide for all or any`
  line `of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the procedure under sub-section (3) of section 8 for the investigation of misbehaviour or`
  line `incapacity of the Chairman, Vice-Chairman or other Member;`
  line
  line `(b) salaries and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service`
  line `(including pension, gratuity and other retirement benefits) of, the Chairman, Vice-Chairman and other`
  line `Members under section 9;`
  line
  line `(c) the financial and administrative powers which the Chairman may exercise over the Benches`
  line `under section 11;`
  line
  line `(d) the salaries and allowances and conditions of service of officers and other employees of the`
  line `Claims Tribunal under sub-section (3) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(e) the form of application, the documents and other evidence to be accompanied with such`
  line `application and fee in respect of filing of such application and fee for the service or execution of`
  line `processes under sub-section (2) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(f) the rules subject to which the Claims Tribunal shall have powers to regulate its own procedure`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 18 and the additional matters in which the Claims Tribunal may`
  line `exercise powers of civil court under clause (i) of sub-section (3) of that section;`
  line
  line `(g) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House`
  line `of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of on effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30_a:
  sectionId (49417)
  sectionNo 30A
  orderNo 32
  title `Power to make rules retrospectively.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 1999, s. 2 (w.e.f. 2-1-1999).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410&sectionId=49417&sectionno=30A&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_1_1_00006_198754_1517807325410
obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[30A. Power to make rules retrospectively.-- The power to make rules under clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 30 shall include the power to make such rules or any of them retrospectively`
  line `from a date not earlier than the date on which this Act received the assent of the President, but no such`
  line `retrospective effect shall be given to any such rule so as to prejudicially affect the interests of any person`
  line `to whom such rule may be applicable.]`
